<section id="_adsm93_" lang="en" class="supplementary-materials"><h3 class="pmc_sec_title">Supplementary Materials</h3>
<section class="sm xbox font-sm" id="db_ds_supplementary-material1_reqid_"><div class="caption p">
<span>Supp tableS1</span><p>SUPP. TABLE S1: Variant Table w/Phenotypic Summary</p>
</div>
<div class="media p"><div class="caption">
<a href="/articles/instance/7484419/bin/NIHMS1617104-supplement-Supp_tableS1.xlsx" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl" class="usa-link">NIHMS1617104-supplement-Supp_tableS1.xlsx</a><sup> (31.1KB, xlsx) </sup>
</div></div></section><section class="sm xbox font-sm" id="db_ds_supplementary-material2_reqid_"><div class="caption p">
<span>supp tableS3</span><p>SUPP. TABLE S3: Variant Summary Table</p>
</div>
<div class="media p"><div class="caption">
<a href="/articles/instance/7484419/bin/NIHMS1617104-supplement-supp_tableS3.xlsx" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl" class="usa-link">NIHMS1617104-supplement-supp_tableS3.xlsx</a><sup> (21.3KB, xlsx) </sup>
</div></div></section><section class="sm xbox font-sm" id="db_ds_supplementary-material3_reqid_"><div class="caption p">
<span>supp mat</span><p>SUPP. FIGURE S1: Visual Acuity Scoring and Diagnosis</p>
<p>eyeGENE<sup>®</sup> Participants Average Visual Acuity Score: Individual participants (indicated by dot) were plotted against average visual acuity score (OD/OS) and color-coded by diagnosis category (Red = Cone rod dystrophy, Gold = Other, Green = Pattern dystrophy, Blue = Retinitis pigmentosa, Purple = Stargardt disease). Figure shows similar visual acuity score range between clinical phenotypes.</p>
<p>SUPP. FIGURE S2: eyeGENE<sup>®</sup> Participant Breakdown of ERG Status and Diagnosis Category</p>
<p>eyeGENE<sup>®</sup> Participant Breakdown of ERG Status and Diagnosis Category: Chart showing the number of participants with a normal or abnormal ERG as designated by diagnosis category.</p>
<p>SUPP. FIGURE S3: <em>PRPH2</em>-positive Fundus Images of Participants 44 (A), 39 (B), and 79 (C)</p>
<p>These fundus images are from participants 44 (A), 39 (B), and 79 (C) who all carry the c.612C&gt;A p.Tyr204* variant. Participants 44 and 79 were diagnosed with Pattern dystrophy and participant 39 was diagnosed with Stargardt disease.</p>
<p>SUPP. FIGURE S4: <em>PRPH2</em>-positive Autofluorescence Images of Participants 59 (A), 61 (B), and 62 (C)</p>
<p>These autofluorescence images are from participants 59 (A), 61 (B), and 62 (C) who all carry the c.422A&gt;G p.Tyr141Cys variant. Participants 59 and 62 were diagnosed with Stargardt disease and participant 61 was diagnosed with Pattern dystrophy.</p>
<p>SUPP. TABLE S2: Descriptive Statistics Table</p>
<p>SUPP. TABLE S4: ERG Data with Diagnosis, Years with Disease, and Age at Exam</p>
</div>
<div class="media p"><div class="caption">
<a href="/articles/instance/7484419/bin/NIHMS1617104-supplement-supp_mat.pdf" data-ga-action="click_feat_suppl" class="usa-link">NIHMS1617104-supplement-supp_mat.pdf</a><sup> (166.3KB, pdf) </sup>
</div></div></section></section></section></section></section></article>

                      

